<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id56a18290-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s906"><num value="906">§ 906.</num><heading> Air Station Cape Cod Improvements</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary may expend funds for the repair, improvement, restoration, or replacement of those federally or nonfederally owned support buildings, including appurtenances, which are on leased or permitted real property constituting Coast Guard Air Station Cape Cod, located on Massachusetts Military Reservation, Cape Cod, Massachusetts.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id56a18291-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/103/206/tIII/s303/a">Pub. L. 103–206, title III, § 303(a)</ref>, <date date="1993-12-20">Dec. 20, 1993</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/107/2423">107 Stat. 2423</ref>, § 671; renumbered § 906, <ref href="/us/pl/115/282/tI/s107/b">Pub. L. 115–282, title I, § 107(b)</ref>, <date date="2018-12-04">Dec. 4, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/4205">132 Stat. 4205</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
